reviews.review_text: Kezar Stadium 73 One of the GEATEST 3 set shows of all time!!Jerry and the boys are RIGHT on the money!!! Best set list of all time!!

- Have to disagree: if you want one of the greatest, you need look no furthur than both of the very next shows at RFK (June 9-10).

The second set here is OK but really nothing special, and Jerry's playing is extremely lazy & lackluster from Half-Step through Truckin and even into the beginning of He's Gone, at which point he suddenly gets a jolt and starts playing like a god again. Erase the entire second set & you've got a five-star show.

i gotta agree at least with the 6/10 that was an absolute monster. this show though holds a sweet spot for me since it was my first tape.only had entire first and highlights of second though. I loved these 2 tapes I had to the graveyard lol. I thought it was a well-played show like most in 73. killer other one and Eyes here for sure.decent Playin but not mind-blowing all in all i'd rate it a 4
The Sun will shine in my backdoor someday.. Had me at HELLO.
